{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["VDB Renormalize SDF"], "type": "title", "extent": [128, 152], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [152, 222], "text": ["Fixes signed distance fields stored in VDB volume primitives."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [16, 105], "text": ["See ", {"text": ["volumes"], "fullpath": "/model/volumes", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/model/volumes"}, " for an explanation of standard volumes and OpenVDB volumes."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [246, 433], "text": ["This node iteratively adjusts the voxel values to properly respect the distance to the zero crossing line. \nThis requires proper signed distance fields for the results to be meaningful."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [439, 701], "text": ["If you have significant departures from a proper signed distance field, you can rebuild it with the ", {"text": ["VDB From Polygons node"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vdbfrompolygons", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/vdbfrompolygons"}, ".\n    That node will implicitly convert an input SDF to polygons, then convert the polygons back to an SDF."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [433, 439], "container": true, "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [721, 849], "text": ["The name(s) of the VDB volume primitives in the input to be normalized.\n    See ", {"fragment": "#group", "text": ["specifying volumes"], "value": "/model/volumes#group", "fullpath": "/model/volumes#group", "scheme": null, "type": "link"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Group"], "role": "item", "extent": [713, 721], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [861, 995], "text": ["The number of rounds of renormalization that should be performed.  More rounds are slower but will result in a more correct SDF."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Iterations"], "role": "item", "extent": [849, 861], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1035, 1155], "text": ["The method for smoothing the SDF after each iteration.\n    Later options in the list are slower but more accurate."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Renorm Accuracy"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "accuracy"}, "extent": [995, 1012], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [701, 713], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1164, 1188], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vdbsmooth", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/vdbsmooth"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1188, 1214], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vdbsmoothsdf", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/vdbsmoothsdf"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1214, 1243], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vdbreshapesdf", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/vdbreshapesdf"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [1155, 1164], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "title": ["VDB Renormalize SDF"], "summary": ["Fixes signed distance fields stored in VDB volume primitives."], "attrs": {"version": null, "tags": "vdb, merge", "since": "12.5", "namespace": null, "verb_since": "16.5", "internal": "vdbrenormalizesdf", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "icon": "COMMON/openvdb"}, "included": ["/nodes/sop/volume_types"], "type": "root"}